<subSubSection lastPageId="95" lastPageNumber="201" pageId="93" pageNumber="199" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="93.[212,270,1472,1496]" box="[212,270,1472,1496]" pageId="93" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis box="[212,270,1472,1496]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="199">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="93.[212,1172,1511,1695]" lastBlockId="94.[144,1104,1609,1697]" lastPageId="94" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="93" pageNumber="199">
Head similar to female except palps are broader and with only three long bristles at tip, the labrum is pale straw yellow and clearly not as broad as diameter of postpedicel, and labella with fine hairs instead of strong teeth on their inner faces. Thorax similar to female. Abdomen with brown tergites and venter. The latter with sternum of fourth segment with a patch of hairs, each of which has its basal socket surrounded by disc of pigment, but these discs do not coalesce to form a distinct sternite. Hypopygium, including anal tube, brown. Legs similar to female except base of hind femur and trochanter as 
<figureCitation box="[439,573,1641,1665]" captionStart="Figure 73" captionStartId="96.[144,211,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,173,1298]" captionTargetId="figure-102@96.[144,1104,173,1299]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="Figure 73. Metopina tanjae. (A) Male, base of right wing. (B) Male, posterior face of base of hind femur and trochanter. (C) Female, abdominal tergites 3–6. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207272" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5207272/files/figure.png" pageId="94" pageNumber="200">Figure 73B</figureCitation>
. Wing 
<quantity box="[659,743,1641,1665]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="94" pageNumber="200" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
long and with basal region as 
<figureCitation box="[144,276,1673,1697]" captionStart="Figure 73" captionStartId="96.[144,211,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,173,1298]" captionTargetId="figure-102@96.[144,1104,173,1299]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="Figure 73. Metopina tanjae. (A) Male, base of right wing. (B) Male, posterior face of base of hind femur and trochanter. (C) Female, abdominal tergites 3–6. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207272" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5207272/files/figure.png" pageId="94" pageNumber="200">Figure 73A</figureCitation>
, otherwise it and haltere similar to female.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207102" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5207102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5207102/files/figure.png" pageId="94" pageNumber="200" startId="94.[144,211,1484,1506]" targetBox="[169,1104,173,1452]" targetPageId="94">
<paragraph blockId="94.[144,1103,1484,1536]" pageId="94" pageNumber="200">
