<taxonomicName box="[261,466,1485,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Metopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heselhausi">
<emphasis box="[261,466,1485,1507]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="200">Metopina heselhausi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male. (A) Right wing. (B) Abdominal tergite 4. (C) Posterior face of base of hind femur and trochanter. Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207106" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5207106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5207106/files/figure.png" pageId="95" pageNumber="201" startId="95.[212,279,968,990]" targetBox="[214,1171,171,936]" targetPageId="95">
<paragraph blockId="95.[212,1172,968,1019]" pageId="95" pageNumber="201">
Figure 72. 
<taxonomicName box="[328,532,968,990]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Metopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="95" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heselhausi">
